    public interface ListCellRenderer

    Defines an interface for objects that can render list cells from a ListModelComponent.

    The idea of a renderer is that the component is used as a "rubber stamp" when the cell is drawn. The same component may be used for several cells, and really should be for best performance. Note that the component is discarded after the cell is drawn, so no state is persisted.

    NOTE: The component returned from the cell renderer method will be referenced using a weak reference. You must hold a strong reference for as long as you need the component. It is recommended to hold the reference as a field in the cell renderer implementation. (Components that implement this interface directly will work fine as the cell renderer is held as a strong reference).

    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

    • Method Detail

      • getListCellRendererComponent

        Component getListCellRendererComponent(ListModelComponent list,
                                       @Nullable java.lang.Object value,
                                       boolean isSelected,
                                       boolean hasFocus,
                                       int row)
        Returns a Component to use for rendering a cell in a ListModelComponent.
        Parameters:
        list - The ListModelComponent that has the data being rendered.
        value - The value of the cell being rendered.
        isSelected - Indicates whether the cell is in a selected state.
        hasFocus - Indicates if the cell has focus, implementations may want to indicate this in the UI.
        row - The row for the cell.
        Returns:
        A Component which can be used to display the value stored in the specified list cell.
